# Accessibility

- All UI MUST pass AXE checks
- Follow WCAG AA minimums:
  - Focus management (visible focus indicators, logical tab order)
  - Color contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
  - ARIA attributes where native semantics are insufficient
  - Keyboard navigability for all interactive elements
- Use semantic HTML elements (`button`, `nav`, `main`, `label`) before reaching for ARIA
- Provide accessible names for icons and icon-only buttons
